// Details for: soundcore-q20i-headphones (Soundcore Q20i, model A3004)
// Lab sheet: CV-EB-A3004-001 — §7.5 ELEVATED gold deepen (Wave Adj/Mid EXTRA+ 4/4).
//   Upgraded from the first protocol-grade bench that already held Timer+ ANC
//   OFF/ON stopwatches, Kkmoon weight, FNB58 charge, BT walk, multipoint, and
//   Egypt field ANC notes. This pass adds sibling A/B ladder hygiene vs Life
//   Q20 (A3025) / Life Q30 (A3028), USB-C + Transparency + multipoint vs
//   Micro-USB classic / hard-case triad clarity, SKU naming hygiene (Q20i ≠
//   Life Q20), and airline cabin note — WITHOUT inventing new dB / ms / SNR
//   and WITHOUT pasting sibling stopwatch rows as this sample's own numbers.
//   Any vendor "% noise reduction" / dB figure = vendor-stated only (§11.3 / §14).
// Wave headphones (over-ear). Physics envelope enforced (§8). §7.5 adapted for
//   over-ear / on-ear: A = full-unit weight (no buds/case split); B = playtime
//   ANC OFF + ANC ON; C/E case steps = N/A (no charging case); D/F = USB-C
//   full + quick charge on the unit; G = BT range; H = multipoint; I = ANC
//   qualitative only (no anechoic / no invented dB); J = mic qualitative
//   (no SNR); K = codecs in Soundcore App; L = latency qualitative (no ms).
// Sibling ladder: Q11i (A3005, no ANC) → Life Q20 (A3025, classic hybrid ANC
//   ON/OFF + Micro-USB + soft pouch, no app/multipoint) → Q20i (A3004, this
//   file — app hybrid ANC + Transparency + USB-C + multipoint + soft pouch)
//   → Life Q30 (A3028, Transport/Indoor/Outdoor + hard case) → Space One /
//   Q45 (Adaptive ANC + LDAC tiers). Sibling files untouched.
// CairoVolt is an INDEPENDENT retailer — not an authorized/official distributor.
// Engineer: Eng. Omar Khaled / م. عمر خالد · testDate 2026-07-24 · New Cairo lab.
// Elevated gold bar: ≥160 lines · 5+5 aiTldr · no invented dB/ms/SNR · SKU hygiene.
// Recall check dated 2026-07-24 — A3004 not on Anker PB/cable recall lists.
